BACKEND — Development Rules
Architecture Rules

- Keep APIs stateless.
- Do not introduce unnecessary microservices.
- Do not add complex aggregation pipelines unless justified.
- Prefer simple enum categories over scoring systems.
- Keep story model audio-first.

Data Rules

- Guest users must never be persisted.
- Listening progress must use upsert logic.
- Mark story complete when progress ≥ 90%.
- Increment play count only after 10 seconds.
- Avoid storing redundant counters unless required.

API Rules

- Use cursor-based pagination only.
- Keep response payload minimal.
- Do not return unused metadata.
- Avoid nested heavy objects in feed responses.
- Maintain consistent response envelope format.

Performance Rules

- All feed queries must be indexed (language, category, createdAt).
- Avoid N+1 query patterns.
- Keep response time target under 300ms.
- Avoid blocking operations in request cycle.
- Use async processing for non-critical updates.

Scope Discipline Rules

- Do not reintroduce coins or withdrawal logic.
- Do not add referral-based features.
- Do not overbuild recommendation engine early.
- Keep AI consoling logic optional and decoupled.
- Every new feature must improve retention or listening time.

These rules will prevent AI from:

- Overcomplicating architecture
- Reintroducing removed systems
- Adding flashy UI noise
- Building scale features before retention

